article.headline: SE Missouri 61, Morehead St. 59
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Michael Rembert's putback with 1.4 seconds left lifted Southeast Missouri to a 61-59 win over Morehead State Wednesday night. Tied at 59-59, Morehead State (10-9, 6-5 Ohio Valley Conference) had the ball with less than 20 seconds remaining. Brandon Foust blocked a Quentin Pryor shot, and Southeast Missouri (8-13, 6-6) got the loose ball to set up the game-winning shot. Terrick Willoughby's 3-point attempt was not good, but Rembert got the rebound and hit the basket. Rembert finished with 18 for the Redhawks. Shaun Williams came off the bench to lead Morehead with 16 points. Cordaryl Ballard had 11, while Brandon Callahan and Vincent Crutcher each added 10. The Eagles struggled from the free-throw line, shooting just 9-of-19 for 47.4 percent. Morehead State led 33-32 at the half before Southeast Missouri State built as big as a 59-51 lead with 4:35 left. The Eagles then reeled off eight straight to tie the game.
